OL,3,CRochester's MP and Bishop set out
OL,4,Copposing views on assisted dying debate
OL,6,FThe private member's bill will mirror
OL,7,Fthe text of a previous proposal by her
OL,8,Fparty colleague Kim Leadbeater, which
OL,9,Fwas twice approved by a majority of
OL,10,FMPs. It ran out of time in the House
OL,11,Fof Lords in April.
OL,13,FSpeaking to ITV News Meridian, the
OL,14,FRochester and Strood MP described
OL,15,Fbringing the bill back to the Commons
OL,16,Fas "a big undertaking" which came with
OL,17,Fa feeling of "huge responsibility".
OL,26,@xD@DOUxD@VO]yD@NOUyD@bO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
