OL,3,CRochester's MP and Bishop set out
OL,4,Copposing views on assisted dying debate
OL,6,FThe Lords had faced accusations of
OL,7,Ffilibustering ` or delaying ` the
OL,8,Fprevious bill after more than 1,200
OL,9,Famendments were put forward, with more
OL,10,Fthan 800 of those tabled or sponsored
OL,11,Fby just seven peers.
OL,13,FMs Edwards said the "proper democratic
OL,14,Fprocess" had been "interrupted" and it
OL,15,Fwas "a point of principle" that the
OL,16,Fbill was given another chance to pass
OL,17,Fboth Houses of Parliament.
OL,26,@vD@HO]wD@EOUwD@ZO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
