CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1784796493
OL,3,CRochester's MP and Bishop set out
OL,4,Copposing views on assisted dying debate
OL,6,FAsked if she was hoping it could be
OL,7,Fpushed through the Lords, Ms Edwards
OL,8,Fsaid: "What I'm seeking to do is to
OL,9,Fsend it back to the House of Lords and
OL,10,Fallow them to finish the job because,
OL,11,Fas a country, we just cannot allow
OL,12,Fthis really important issue to not be
OL,13,Faddressed."
OL,15,FThe rarely used Parliament Act, allows
OL,16,Ffor bills that have been backed by the
OL,17,FCommons in two successive sessions but
OL,18,Frejected by peers to pass into law
OL,19,Fwithout Lords approval.
OL,26,@pD@GOUuD@KO]
